# STACK CONVENTIONS

## Version Pins (Phase 1)

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|------------|---------|
| Backend | Laravel | 12.x |
| Runtime | PHP | 8.2+ |
| Frontend | Svelte | 5.x |
| Bridge | Inertia.js | v2 (`@inertiajs/svelte` ^2.x) |
| Styling | TailwindCSS | 4.x |
| Components | Skeleton UI | 4.x |
| Database | MariaDB | 10.6+ |
| Real-time | Laravel Reverb | Latest |
| JS Runtime | Node.js | 20+ |

## Critical Anti-Patterns (NEVER DO)

1. **SvelteKit patterns** ŌĆö No `+page.svelte`, `+layout.svelte`, load functions, `$app/*` imports, or form actions. This is an Inertia app.
2. **Svelte 4 syntax** ŌĆö No `on:click`, `createEventDispatcher`, `<slot>`, or `export let`. Use Svelte 5 runes.
3. **Skeleton theme** ŌĆö Use `@import '@skeletonlabs/skeleton'` and custom theme in `resources/css/app.css`; set `data-theme="flexiqueue"` on `<html>`. Do not configure Skeleton in tailwind.config.js.
4. **Business logic in controllers** ŌĆö Controllers are thin. Use Service classes in `app/Services/`.
5. **Skipping Form Requests** ŌĆö All API endpoints use Form Request classes for validation.
6. **Raw DB facade** ŌĆö Use Eloquent models, not `DB::table()` for domain queries.
7. **API-only routes for pages** ŌĆö Use `Inertia::render()` for pages, not JSON responses.
8. **Stores for page data** ŌĆö Page data comes via `$props()` from Inertia, not Svelte stores.

## File Naming Conventions

| Type | Location | Naming |
|------|----------|--------|
| Controllers | `app/Http/Controllers/` | `PascalCaseController.php` |
| Services | `app/Services/` | `NameService.php` |
| Form Requests | `app/Http/Requests/` | `VerbNounRequest.php` |
| Models | `app/Models/` | `PascalCase.php` (singular) |
| Svelte Pages | `resources/js/Pages/{Section}/` | `Index.svelte`, `Show.svelte`, `Edit.svelte` |
| Svelte Components | `resources/js/Components/` | `PascalCase.svelte` |
| Layouts | `resources/js/Layouts/` | `NameLayout.svelte` |

## Component System

- **Theme**: FlexiQueue custom Skeleton theme in `resources/css/themes/flexiqueue.css`; see `docs/architecture/07-UI-UX-SPECS.md` and `SKELETON-COMPONENT-MAPPING.md`
- **UI approach**: Stay on Skeleton + flexiqueue theme; use incremental UI improvements only (no full ui-kit migration).
- **Reference**: See `public/dev/components.html` for live component examples
- **Spec**: See `docs/architecture/07-UI-UX-SPECS.md` for design tokens and patterns
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 48x48px for mobile (staff phones)

## Quick Checks Before Committing

- [ ] No SvelteKit imports (`$app/`, `+page`, `+layout`)
- [ ] Using Svelte 5 runes (`$state`, `$derived`, `$props`, `onclick`)
- [ ] Controllers return `Inertia::render()` not JSON
- [ ] Form validation in Form Request class
- [ ] Business logic in Service class
